<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource="User" Background="White" Name="flowDoc"
xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16" xml:lang="de-de">
            <Span.TextDecorations>
                <TextDecoration Location="Underline" />
            </Span.TextDecorations> Using the "Internet frame generator" plugin (IFG)
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">This IFG plugin offers the possibility to create either
            Internet Protocol packets ("IPv4 packets") or Address Resolution Protocol packets ("ARP
            request packets"). ARP request packets are used to request the Media Access
            Control (MAC) address corresponding to a certain IP address. This happens, when an Ethernet
            interface wants to send a message to a certain IP address, but doesn't have the corresponding
            MAC address. The ARP response message contains this MAC address belonging to the specified IP
            address. Each Ethernet device has such a unique MAC address, consisting of 6 bytes (or 48 bits).
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">You can choose the kind of packets
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">- either in the</Span>
        <Span FontStyle="Italic" xml:lang="de-de">Algorithm Settings</Span>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">(within the drop-down menu "Kind of packet"):
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="192" Height="224" Source="/Internet_frame_generator;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/IFG_AS_KOP.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">- or by right clicking on the plugin in the editor:
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="260" Height="170" Source="/Internet_frame_generator;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/IFG_Settings_rightClick.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">Please note: This plugin supports only ARP request packets, ARP response packets
            can't be created.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">You can also adjust how many packets are going to be created. This can only be done within the
        </Span>
        <Span FontStyle="Italic" xml:lang="de-de">Algorithm Settings</Span>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">by entering the according number in the text field "Number of packets":</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="192" Height="243" Source="/Internet_frame_generator;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/IFG_AS_NOP.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">You can enter a value between 1 and 100,000 packets. If you try
            to type in a invalid value, e.g. a number grater than 100,000 or a character, an error will occur:
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="192" Height="242" Source="/Internet_frame_generator;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/IFG_AS_NOP_Error.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">Now let's have a look on how you can use this IFG plugin. This plugin is part
            of a prepared workspace, which you can find in the CrypTool 2.0 SampleProjects folder. It's called
            "AttackWEP-01.cte" and provides the following workflow:</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The packets, which are created within this plugin, are delivered
            to the "WEP protocol" plugin, which encrypts the packets according to the WEP protocol (for details,
            please have a look at the description tab of the "WEP protocol" plugin). Those encrypted packets are then
            delivered to the "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin, which simulates one of three provided attacks
            against the WEP protocol (for details, please have a look at the description tab of the "Attacks on the WEP
            protocol" plugin).</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The following plugins are involved in the chain (besides the above mentioned
            ones): The "TextInput" plugin, the "Number Input" plugin, the "Multiplexer" plugin and the
            "IncDec" plugin. The "TextInput" provides the key, which is used within the "WEP protocol" plugin
            for the encryption operation.</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="522" Height="266" Source="/Internet_frame_generator;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/SW_AWEP.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The packets, which are encrypted by the "WEP protocol" plugin, are
            delivered to the "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin. This plugin tries to recover the key,
            which has been used to encrypt the packets. There are three attacks possible: The "FMS attack",
            the "KoreK attack" and the "PTW attack" (for details, please have a look at the description tab of the
            "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin).</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">If the recovery of this key has not been successful with the number of packets
            adjusted in this IFG plugin, the "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin forwards the value "false"
            at one of it's output. This value goes to the "Multiplexer" plugin, which decides whether the number
            provided by the "IncDec" plugin will be forwarded or not. If the value, provided by the "Attacks on the
            WEP protocol" plugin, is "false", the "Multiplexer" plugin will forward the incremented integer value.
            This incremented value is also forwarded to this IFG plugin, which will then create the requested packet in
            the requested amount once again. If the value provided from the "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin is
            "true", the "Multiplexer" plugin will forward nothing, and the chain stops working.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">So this workflow is a loop, which doesn't stop until the key has been recovered
            successfully.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph />
</FlowDocument>
